Was alerted to the existence of this bar by another yelper and decided to check it out while waiting for a spot at Champs Diner across the street. I feel like this is a sort of well established tradition for Champs patrons since there always seems to be a wait!  One of the best things about this bar is that they have happy hour till 9pm! That by itself is super generous but they one up themselves by offering  $4 beers, $5 well drinks and $6 cocktails so basically everything is half price. The have a great beer list but decided to go with the cocktails and have to say I was very impressed. Their version to the manhattan was fantastic and I felt like for $6 I was basically robbing them. Was so good I had 2 even though was planning to have just 1 drink.  I wanted to give them a 5 star review but the place is cash only which I absolutely detest, especially at a bar. Makes everything so much more complicated than it needs to be. Place was packed at 8:30pm on a Wednesday night and I can definitely see why. They have a patio out back too for when the weather is nice.
